-- Tiger Woods Enters Bridgestone as PGA Tuneup, Seeking Eighth Championship
-- Larry Siddons
-- 2010-07-28T18:43:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/tiger-woods-enters-bridgestone-as-pga-tuneup-seeking-eighth-championship.html

          
          
             Tiger Woods will play in the
Bridgestone Invitational in Akron, Ohio, next week, before his
final shot at a major golf title this season.  
 Woods listed the World Golf Championships event at
Firestone Country Club on the playing scheduled posted on his
website. He has won the tournament seven times, a PGA Tour
record for an event at a single course. The tournament runs Aug.
5-8.  
 Starting Aug. 12, Woods will be at the PGA Championship,
the season’s final major, at Whistling Straits Golf Club in
Kohler, Wisconsin. He is four titles behind Jack Nicklaus’s
record of 18 professional majors.  
          
          


  


        